# Project Structure Overview

## Main Directories

- `_components/` - Reusable React components
- `app/` - Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- `pages/api/` - API routes (Pages Router)
- `lib/` - Utility functions and shared logic
- `models/` - Data models and schemas
- `types/` - TypeScript type definitions
- `scripts/` - Maintenance and migration scripts

## App Router Structure

- `(clientPortal)` - Client portal route group
- `(publicGroup)` - Public routes (sign-in, etc.)
- `(root)` - Main application routes
- `acceptToken` - Token acceptance flow

## Component Categories

- **Client Portal**: Client-facing access and dashboard
- **Dashboard**: Main application dashboard components
- **Database**: Client management and data display
- **Estimates**: Estimate creation and management
- **Invoices**: Invoice generation and management
- **Payroll**: Employee payroll management
- **Schedule**: Job scheduling and calendar
- **PDF**: PDF generation utilities

## File Organization Principles

- Group related functionality together
- Maintain clear separation of concerns
- Use consistent naming patterns
- Keep files focused on single responsibilities
